{
  "texts": [
    "In other words, the aspects and sentiments to be predicted can be considered corrupted tokens in the input.",
    "To make the modified input more natural, the sentiment labels are mapped to the corresponding label words, i.e., neutral to ok, positive to great and negative to bad.",
    "Domain adaptive pretraining (DAPT) was proposed by Gururangan et al.",
    "DAPT pretrains on a large-scale unlabeled corpus related to the domain and then fine-tunes specific tasks, which can bridge the domain gap.",
    "In the attribute-grained preference analysis task, the language model is pretrained via text-filling targets on an indomain corpus, as shown in Fig. 5."
  ]
}